      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> These two rhetorical questions emphasize that both their ancestors and the prophets who proclaimed Yahweh’s message to their ancestors have died. The questions can be translated as a statement. Alternate translation: [Neither your fathers nor the prophets are here because they have all died.]
