      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> These phrases refer to the man who “was riding on a red horse” in Zechariah 1:8. This could mean: (1) the man dismounted his horse and stood or (2) the word “stood” is an idiom that means he was located in that position. Alternate translation: [the man who was among the myrtle trees]
